<subSubSection id="7B8E65470114FF9FFF6ECDE49C62C213" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="219" pageId="4" pageNumber="218" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="332B36CC0114FF9FFF6ECDE49C62C213" blockId="4.[136,1451,2021,2084]" lastBlockId="5.[136,1452,158,292]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="219" pageId="4" pageNumber="218">
<emphasis id="01E0EADE0114FF9EFF6ECDE49C42C4C8" bold="true" box="[189,256,2021,2047]" pageId="4" pageNumber="218">Notes</emphasis>
: Natural hybrids between 
<taxonomicName id="F4944D4F0114FF9EFDFFCDE49F9FCB37" box="[556,733,2021,2048]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Scrophulariaceae" genus="Verbascum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="218" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="01E0EADE0114FF9EFDFFCDE49FE5C4C8" box="[556,679,2021,2047]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="218">Verbascum</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
are readily produced when species coexist, whereas all hitherto described hybrid taxa are invariably sterile (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="57054B3D0114FF9EFD6BC2089E23CB14" author="Murbeck, S. S." box="[696,865,2057,2083]" pageId="4" pageNumber="218" refId="ref3647" refString="Murbeck, S. S. (1933) Monographie der Gattung Verbascum. H. Ohlsson, Lund, 630 pp." type="book" year="1933">Murbeck 1933</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="57054B3D0114FF9EFCBDC20899AFCB13" author="Huber-Morath, A. &amp; Rechinger, K. H." box="[878,1261,2057,2084]" pageId="4" pageNumber="218" pagination="42 - 55" refId="ref3458" refString="Huber-Morath, A. &amp; Rechinger, K. H. (1960) Zur Kenntnis der Gattungen Verbascum und Celsia in Griechenland. Mitteilungen des Thuringischen Botanischen Vereins 2: 42 - 55." type="journal article" year="1960">Huber-Morath &amp; Rechinger 1960</bibRefCitation>
). It is also noted that, unlike 
<emphasis id="01E0EADE0115FF9FFED9CA9E9CF1C38F" box="[266,435,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="219">V. × sipiadense</emphasis>
, the parental species 
<taxonomicName id="F4944D4F0115FF9FFD4CCA9E9E5FC38F" authorityName="Fraas" authorityYear="1845" box="[671,797,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Scrophulariaceae" genus="Verbascum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="219" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="limnense">
<emphasis id="01E0EADE0115FF9FFD4CCA9E9E5FC38F" box="[671,797,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="219">V. limnense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
always exhibits white stamen hairs, not violet ones as cited in former literature (
<bibRefCitation id="57054B3D0115FF9FFEA2CAC39F5DC3EB" author="Ferguson, I. K." box="[369,543,194,220]" pageId="5" pageNumber="219" pagination="205 - 216" refId="ref3020" refString="Ferguson, I. K. (1972) Verbascum L. In: Tutin, T. G., Heywood, V. H., Burges, N. A., Moore, D. M., Valentine, D. H., Walters, S. M. &amp; Webb, D. A. (Eds.) Flora Europaea 3. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge, pp. 205 - 216." type="book chapter" year="1972">Ferguson 1972</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="57054B3D0115FF9FFDFFCAC39FF4C3EB" author="Trigas, P." box="[556,694,194,220]" pageId="5" pageNumber="219" refId="ref3910" refString="Trigas, P. (2003) Contribution to the study of the endemism of the flora of the island of Evvia. PhD Thesis, University of Patras, Greece, 341 pp. [in Greek with an English summary]." type="book" year="2003">Trigas 2003</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="57054B3D0115FF9FFD10CAC39E0EC3EA" author="Strid, A." box="[707,844,194,221]" pageId="5" pageNumber="219" pagination="1 - 700" refId="ref3850" refString="Strid, A. (2016 a) Atlas of the Aegean flora, Part 1: Texts and Plates. Englera 33 (1): 1 - 700." type="journal article" year="2016">Strid 2016a</bibRefCitation>
). It is thus hypothesized that the various descriptions of 
<taxonomicName id="F4944D4F0115FF9FFF79CAE69C6FC237" authorityName="Fraas" authorityYear="1845" box="[170,301,230,256]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Scrophulariaceae" genus="Verbascum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="219" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="limnense">
<emphasis id="01E0EADE0115FF9FFF79CAE69C6FC237" box="[170,301,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="219">V. limnense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in previous floras might have been partially based on heterologous material consisting of the new nothospecies.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
